[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] In general $\sigma$ is the **abscissa of convergence** of a Dirichlet series if it converges for $\Re (s)>\sigma$ and diverges for $\Re (s)<\sigma .$ This is the analogue for Dirichlet series of the radius of convergence for power series.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] The Dirichlet series case is more complicated, though: absolute convergence and uniform convergence may occur in distinct half-planes.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] In many cases, the analytic function associated with a Dirichlet series has an analytic extension to a larger domain.
