[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] The formal Dirichlet series form a ring Ω, indeed an *R*-algebra, with the zero function as additive zero element and the function *δ* defined by *δ*(1) = 1, *δ*(*n*) = 0 for *n* > 1 as multiplicative identity.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] An element of this ring is invertible if *a*(1) is invertible in *R*.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] If *R* is commutative, so is Ω; if *R* is an integral domain, so is Ω.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] The non-zero multiplicative functions form a subgroup of the group of units of Ω.
[src:mellin-transform/dirichlet-series] The ring of formal Dirichlet series over **C** is isomorphic to a ring of formal power series in countably many variables.
